# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Poultry Hero frontend — PRODUCTION env example (Vite).
#
# Copy to frontend/.env.production (or pass these as build-time env vars) when
# building for production. NEVER commit a real .env file.
#
# Data hygiene: production builds must NOT use mock/hardcoded business data.
# Leave VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false (or unset — it defaults to false) so the app
# runs in live-API mode. Only set it to true for local UI development.
#
# NOTE: even if VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=true were set, a production build
# (`vite build`, import.meta.env.PROD === true) forces mock mode OFF in code
# (frontend/src/services/config.ts). The deploy script also refuses to build
# with VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=true. See docs/deployment/PRODUCTION_MOCK_DATA_AUDIT.md.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_API_BASE=https://poultryhero.solutions/api
VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false
